Thankfully the umpire did not have to ask for 'new balls, please' after this uncomfortable incident at the Australian Open on Thursday in Melbourne. 

Instead of a line judge calling 'out!', it was a case of shouting 'ouch!' after a ferocious serve from Spain's Feliciano Lopez hit a stunned ball boy right where it hurts.

The unfortunate ball boy got in the way of Lopez's 200km/h serve during the first set of his match with Frenchman Adrian Mannarino, and had no chance of getting out of the way before it thumped into the tenderest of regions.

